      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the same metric used in the clinical acceptance threshold and in the bench validation experiments. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time) are directly used in the power-law hemolysis model. QoI mapping to clinical endpoint is fully documented. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
